race.comment: Wide open. BELLA ANGELICA (9) was placed on debut then well off best last time when started favourite but dropped out in the straight. Freshened, won a trial since and has the blinkers added. Trained here and worth another try. IBERIAN LYNX (3) has looked close to a win with a fresh-up placing then a fourth latest. Has good early speed and fitter again will take catching.  DIRNASEER (4) had two starts almost a year ago and has been off the scene since. Has had six jump-outs since then coming back into work but not racing in the autumn, and presents after three solid jump-outs leading to return. Should be primed to run well.  LANTANA (14) was well fancied on debut but faded out of it and ran below expectations. That has proven a hot form race though and given time and back to home track. Worth another go.
